"Keep three wishes handy,/In case you chance to meet/Any day a Leprechaun/Coming down the street."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubaggley.showPublicProfile?language=EN>baggley</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.nwlink.com/~jmc/wolf_2.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/26/00 6:54:03 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.nwlink.com/~jmc/wolf_2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Lepreckon ...  Pulling to the beach tips</span><hr size=1> I am sorry you have had trouble pulling these guys out to the beach, I truly think that they become MUCH easier to handle once you get them out of the water.<br>
<br>
So, here's my  Surf -&gt; Turf  guide  :)<br>
<br>
ok your on the bottom of the lake, you swim up to, and aggro the Gobs, no need to cast a spell, just smack the little buggers.<br>
<br>
Next swim straight up to the surface ( be careful if your under one of the two platforms, the ones with the roofs ) you don't want to swim up underneath the platform and get stuck ~trust me~<br>
<br>
The Gobs are going to be right behind smacking ya all the way, they swim faster that you do.<br>
<br>
when you get to the surface run a SHORT distance across the surface of the lake (with lev) turn 180 deg  and LOOK for the gobs, you will see their tags or their heads. run backwards !!<br>
<br>
Running backwards slows you down a bit, but in wolfform you are faster running backwards (with lev) than the gobs are swimming.  so you can watch them !!!  all the way to the beach !!<br>
<br>
I ALWAYS used this approach you can slow down if you are starting to get too far ahead of them.<br>
<br>
One more point here,  if the Gobs are too widely spaced run a big circle around them, or a oval, or Z pattern, to group them up !!<br>
<br>
You want to have a place in mind to pull them too in advance, so who cares if you can't see where your going, your gonna get to the beach..  just want to be sure you keep the Gobs close to you.<br>
<br>
next ..  where to pull ?<br>
<br>
Pull them to a nice wide open spot...  You know where the river meets the lake, standing in river, facing lake, take a right on the shore, run a short distance on the shore untill it opens up into an open flat clearing. This is the best spot I have personally found to kite, lots of room, seldom found other PCs in this area.<br>
<br>
Have fun !!!<br>
